OL,5,FSnowdonia National Park, the Cambrian
OL,6,FMountains, and moor land areas across
OL,7,Fcentral Wales, upland areas of the
OL,8,FBrecon Beacons and Black Mountains all
OL,9,Ftypically experience a mild grass
OL,10,Fpollen season. This is mainly because
OL,11,Fupland grasses produce less pollen.
OL,13,FHigh Pollen Count AreasJThe growing
OL,14,Fseasons can be long especially in the
OL,15,Fsouth. From Pembroke in the west to
OL,16,FCardiff in the east and up to 40 miles
OL,17,Finland, the grass pollen count can be
OL,18,Fvery high in June and July.
